<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Their" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Their,</orth> poss. pron. of the third pers. plur.: <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl>. 44 <cit><quote>(each leaning on their elbows).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 20" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 20</bibl> 532 etc. <cit><quote>God send every one their heart's desire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Picardy hath slain their governors,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 89</bibl></cit>. Superfluous: <cit><quote>tears show their love, but want their remedies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.203" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 203</bibl></cit>.
